Q3.1:
Round 1

Your prompt for this round: You live in the south part of Cambridge and you have a limited amount of money. You would like however to take out your children to eat at an Asian restaurant. If you need to travel a bit to get there, that's OK.

Now switch to the recommendation system to pick the right restaurant for your family. Once you have completed your dialogue with the system, switch back to the survey, ask your supervisor to restart the conversation and proceed to the next page.
Q4.1:
Round 2

Your prompt for this round: You are relatively wealthy and you prefer expensive restaurants. You are taking your partner out on a romantic date, and you are both in the mood to eat Mediterranean food.

Now switch to the recommendation system to pick the right restaurant for you and your date. Once you have completed your dialogue with the system, switch back to the survey, ask your supervisor to restart the conversation and proceed to the next page.
Q5.1:
Round 3

Your prompt for this round: You live in the city center of Cambridge, and you don't care about how much your meal costs. You would like to find a busy Halal restaurant nearby where you would probably need to book specific seats in advance.

Now switch to the recommendation system to pick the right restaurant for your upcoming dinner. Once you have completed your dialogue with the system, switch back to the survey, ask your supervisor to restart the conversation and proceed to the next page.
